            rdfs:subClassOf :Nymph ;
            rdfs:seeAlso <https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q165938> ;
            skos:definition "THE HESPERIDES were the goddess-nymphs of evening and the golden light of sunsets. They were the daughters of either Nyx (Night) or the heaven-bearing Titan Atlas. The Hesperides were entrusted with the care of the tree of the golden apples which was had been presented to the goddess Hera by Gaia (the Earth) on her wedding day." ;
            skos:prefLabel "Hesperides"@en ,
                           "Héspérides"@fr .


